please help anyone familiar with autism concerning my toddler my baby boy just turned months and diagnosed with autism i waited months for appointment with developmental pediatrician it was a disaster he was arrogant and ignorant and i went home and cried the whole night my son is in early intervention and receiving aba and ot days a week i have also enrolled him in a program at local hospital and he will start in september they will start him with one day a week they only take five children and its one on one and it is aba and they play and sing and eat lunch there this doctor told me i am not doing enough for my son and i should have him in outside therapies too ei says that no he is getting enough in ei and it would be overwhelming as well as very costly to go outside ei for more treatment i am very blessed as i have another appt tommorrow at another developmental ped who had a cancellation for nd opinion danny lost speech stims a lot and no response to name not sure where he is on spectrum advice hi i am the mother of boys my oldest is now and has pervasive developmental disorder one of the autism spectrum disorders as a little one he went to a therapeutic preschool everyday received speech and ot he is currently going into a self contained junior high class it is very hard to find credible professionals at times i just want to say don't settle for ignorant arrogant doctors or let them make you feel guilty i too have been there unless this doctor has a child with special needs i feel it is very hard for them to grasp the family dynamics of having an autistic child i too had to turn away services because we could not afford them or they were just too inconvenient with rest of my family i find that all too often doctors are too quick to criticize or speak out of ignorance keep searching until you find the right doctors for you and your son in the future you will need support and guidance from many fields don't let anyone tell you what you should be doing you know 